Step-by-step project creation roadmap (from scratch → complete Hybrid RBAC)
Phase 0 — Foundation (Day 0–1)

Create Spring Boot project

Dependencies: Web, Security, Validation, Data JPA, PostgreSQL, Flyway, Lombok, Cache (Caffeine), Actuator

Create base modules

platform package (public schema APIs)

tenant package (tenant schema APIs)

security package (filters, jwt, permission)

multitenancy package (TenantContext, resolver, connection provider)

Deliverable: app starts, DB connection works, Flyway runs.

Phase 1 — Database Migrations (Day 1–2)

Flyway migrations

db/migration/public/V1__init_public.sql

db/migration/tenant/V1__init_tenant.sql

Public schema tables

meta_admin, company_details, subscription, tenant_user_map

seravion_users, seravion_user_roles

Tenant schema template tables

users, roles, user_roles, modules, actions

role_module_action_permission, user_permission (optional)

tenant_security_state

Deliverable: public schema created; tenant template migrations ready.

Phase 2 — Authentication (Day 2–4)

JWT module

JwtService (issue/validate)

Two token types: PLATFORM and TENANT

Security Filter Chains (two chains)

Chain A: /platform/** → validates platform JWT

Chain B: /tenant/** → validates tenant JWT + sets TenantContext

Auth endpoints

POST /platform/auth/register (MetaAdmin)

POST /platform/auth/login (MetaAdmin + Seravion)

POST /tenant/auth/login (tenant users, after provisioning)

Deliverable: platform login returns platform JWT; tenant login returns tenant JWT.

Phase 3 — Tenant Resolution + Multi-tenancy (Day 4–6)

TenantContext

ThreadLocal<String> with default "public"

Hibernate schema switching

CurrentTenantIdentifierResolver

MultiTenantConnectionProvider

JWT → TenantContext

Tenant JWT filter extracts schema claim and sets context per request

Deliverable: tenant endpoints automatically query correct schema.

Phase 4 — Platform Onboarding Flow (Day 6–9)

Company registration

POST /platform/company (creates company_details, status SUBMITTED)

Provider approval

POST /platform/company/{id}/approve (ROLE_SERAVION)

POST /platform/company/{id}/reject (ROLE_SERAVION)

Subscription

POST /platform/subscription/purchase

mark ACTIVE (simulate payment for now)

Deliverable: approved company + active subscription record exists.

Phase 5 — Tenant Provisioning (Day 9–12)

Schema name generator

tenant_<3letters>_SER_<hash>

Provision tenant

Create schema

Run tenant Flyway migrations on that schema

Seed tenant RBAC

Insert base modules, actions

Insert roles: TENANT_CEO, etc.

Insert all permissions for TENANT_CEO

Create tenant CEO user

Copy from public.meta_admin

Assign role TENANT_CEO in user_roles

Write mapping

Insert into public.tenant_user_map

Deliverable: tenant schema exists + CEO user exists in tenant.

Phase 6 — Token Exchange (Day 12–13)

Tenant token exchange endpoint

POST /platform/auth/tenant-token

Input: platform JWT

Checks:

company APPROVED

subscription ACTIVE and not expired

mapping exists

Output: tenant JWT with {uid, schema, roles}

Deliverable: CEO can obtain tenant token and call /tenant/**.

Phase 7 — Dynamic Authorization (Hybrid RBAC) (Day 13–17)

PermissionService (@perm.can)

Cache key: schema:userId:permissionVersion

Loads permissions on miss:

from role permissions

apply user overrides (DENY > ALLOW)

Permission queries

Native queries for:

role perms for user

user overrides for user

permission_version bump

Implement bump in service layer OR DB triggers (preferred)

Trigger on:

user_roles

role_module_action_permission

user_permission

Deliverable: @PreAuthorize("@perm.can(...)") works and updates apply immediately.

Phase 8 — RBAC Management APIs (Day 17–22)

Modules/Actions management

POST /tenant/rbac/modules

POST /tenant/rbac/actions

Role management

POST /tenant/rbac/roles

PUT /tenant/rbac/roles/{id}

Role permission assignment

PUT /tenant/rbac/roles/{id}/permissions

User role assignment

PUT /tenant/users/{id}/roles

User overrides

PUT /tenant/users/{id}/permissions (ALLOW/DENY)

Secure these endpoints with:

@PreAuthorize("hasRole('TENANT_CEO') or @perm.can(authentication,'RBAC','MANAGE')")

Deliverable: full UI/API capability to manage RBAC.

Phase 9 — Production hardening (Day 22+)

Audit logging

log: who changed permissions, when, before/after

Subscription gating on tenant requests

tenant filter checks subscription still ACTIVE

Rate limiting for auth endpoints

Tests

unit: permission evaluation logic

integration: multi-tenant schema routing

security tests: 403/401 scenarios

Observability

Actuator metrics for cache hit rate, auth failures, permission checks

Deliverable: stable, secure, measurable RBAC system.
